Cardinal Francis George died on Friday at age 78 . 
  George was appointed by Pope John Paul II in 1997 to lead the Chicago Archdiocese . 
  Cardinal Francis George was remembered as a man of deep faith, intellect and compassion . 
  He died on April 17 after a long battle with kidney cancer . 
  He was buried on Thursday at Holy Name Cathedral in Chicago . 
  Hundreds of clergy from around the country attended his funeral Mass . 
  George died of kidney cancer last week . 
  He led the nation's third-largest archdiocese and was known as a vigorous defender of Roman Catholic orthodoxy . 
 